sentences.english: Jeremy's eyes widened as he looked down at the city lights.
sentences.chinese: 杰瑞米的眼睛睁得很大，眺望这个城市的灯光。

sentences.english: Climbers Brian Hall and Jerry "Nikko" Cooke have been on Mount Hood for 12 days.
sentences.chinese: 布赖恩豪尔和杰瑞尼克库克在胡德山中已经12天了。

sentences.english: Jerry wanted to introduce himself to Helen, but he didn't want to come on too strong.
sentences.chinese: 杰瑞想要向海伦自我介绍，但他不想表现得太猴急。

sentences.english: Jerry sold the car to someone else yesterday.
sentences.chinese: 昨天杰瑞把车卖给别人了。

sentences.english: Jerry is the cleverest student in the class.
sentences.chinese: 杰瑞是他们班最聪明的学生。

sentences.english: I should've stayed home and watched the Jerry Lewis Telethon .
sentences.chinese: 我该待在家里看《杰瑞刘易斯电视马拉松》的。

sentences.english: Jeremy grinned as he sipped his last sip of milk.
sentences.chinese: 杰瑞米喝完最后一滴牛奶，咧嘴一笑。

sentences.english: Jerry hasbeen my bodyguard on Sunday nights for a long time past and I amused to him.
sentences.chinese: 很久以来杰瑞就是我星期日晚上的保镖，习惯了。

sentences.english: Jerry eats candy bars everyday because he has a sweet tooth.
sentences.chinese: 杰瑞天天吃好几条巧克力棒，因为他对甜食情有独钟。

sentences.english: AttitudeJerry is the kind of guy you love to hate.
sentences.chinese: 杰瑞是那种我最妒恨的人。

sentences.english: In the baseball game, Jerrys foul played into the opponents hands.
sentences.chinese: 棒球比赛中，杰瑞的犯规让对手占了便宜。

sentences.english: This year's winner in Vegas , Jerry Yang, qualified the same way.
sentences.chinese: 今年的维加斯扑克冠军杰瑞杨的晋级之路也是如此。

sentences.english: Jeremy was quiet as his mother tucked him in that evening.
sentences.chinese: 晚上，杰瑞米很安静，妈妈把他放下睡觉。

sentences.english: Jeremy's mother stroked his blond hair as she gently kissed him on the cheek.
sentences.chinese: 妈妈抚摸着杰瑞米金色的头发，轻轻地吻着他的脸颊。
